[According to the EU's Animal Disease Notification System (ADNS) last available issue (24 Apr 2013), bTB has been reported from the following countries since 1 Jan 2013:
Country / Last outbreak date / Number of outbreaks
Austria / 21 Feb 2013 / 2
Belgium / 10 Apr 2013 / 5 (now 6)
France / 18 Apr 2013 / 46
Germany / 18 Apr 2013 / 24
Netherlands / 5 Mar 2013 / 1
Poland / 25 Mar 2013 / 4
Switzerland / 21 Mar 2013 / 2
Total: 84

The requirements from a country to qualify as free from bTB are stipulated in OIE's terrestrial Code, article 11.6.2., available at http://www.oie.int/index.php?id=169&L=0&htmfile=chapitre_1.11.6.htm. As long as the country maintains its bTB-freedom in at least 99.8 per cent of the herds and 99.9 per cent of the cattle, its national bTB-free status recognition is maintained. Such is the situation in relation to Belgium. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/6Fp7.]
